<br>
::Flashing a dazzling smile to Hades everyone else at the banquet, she daintily sipped her wine and bit into a piece of beef happily. She wasn't as happy and cheery as she appeared to be, but she knew that her happiness made Hades happy. And if Hades was happy, then all the other gods of the underworld were happy too; And that particular day, she wanted everyone to be happy. After finishing a first plate, Persephone flew like a social butterfly into conversation with the other gods and godesses, preferably the ones she used to fear the most seeing now how they appreciated her just as much as anyone in the upperworld would::<br>
